args:
After Fjorm puts a stop to the clash between
Alfonse and the prince, the two of them agree
to put the misunderstanding behind them and
become allies. Just then, the imperial army
appears and launches an attack.
They're even stronger than I thought...\nI'm not going to make it...
I don't want to kill you! Surrender!

(I suppose I COULD surrender now that
I've bought Veronica enough time—
although she will likely be very cross
at me for doing so.)

(Or... Hmm. That sandy-haired swordsman
is clearly their leader. If I inflict a heavy
wound on him, that should allow me
enough time to make my escape.)
I'll not allow you to harm His Highness!
I ain't a fan of gangin' up on somebody\nin a fight, but this joker clearly don't\nknow when he's been beat!
Oh for the love of... How many new people\nare we gonna meet today?!
It is good to see you safe, Prince Alfonse.
Might I ask who you are?
I beg you to listen to what I have to say,\nPrince {player_name}. See...
...Okay, so you all came here from\nanother world?
I suppose from your perspective,\nthat would be accurate.
I am Fjorm, and I am—well, WAS—\na princess of the Nifl Kingdom.
Alas, my homeland was ravaged\nby a fearsome enemy.
My apologies if I brought up\na painful memory.
I do not mind. However, because of this,\nI presently reside in the kingdom of\nPrince Alfonse.
Er, that would be me.\nI am Prince Alfonse of Askr.
I've never heard of either of\nyour kingdoms before.
Just as we had never heard of\nAlberia or Dyrenell before this day.
Guess that's one point for the whole\n＂other world＂ theory, yeah?
You guys are taking this REALLY well.\nIf I got sent to another world, I'd probably\nbe runnin' in circles and screaming.
Where we come from, such unexpected\ndetours are not so uncommon.
Where we come from, there are countless\ngateways that open onto other worlds.
So you can travel back and forth\nbetween worlds at will?
I suppose that's about the size of it.
So are ya pals with that lady\nwhat took off earlier?
In a way, yes. Her name is Veronica,\nand she is the princess of the\nEmblian Empire.
Then why is she commanding\nthe Dyrenell forces?
I fear the person you saw was, in fact,\nsomeone who assumed the appearance\nof Princess Veronica.
Wanna run that by me again?
There is an individual with such\ncapabilities in our world.
By the gods... LOKI is here?!
I'm afraid so. I saw her shortly after\narriving in this world.
She was traveling alongside the soldiers\nof this ＂Dyrenell Empire.＂
I cannot believe she is also here...\nThis bodes most ill indeed.
So this lady's...what? Master of disguise?\nGot a killer collection of masks and wigs\nor whatever?
It is no mean disguise; Loki can transform\ninto a perfect imitation of those whose\nform she is assuming.
I wish I could do that! I'd totally act like\nthe prince and order everybody to make\nme cakes and stuff. Mmm...
And you think the person we saw was this\nLoki character assuming Veronica's form?
This day is gettin' weirder by the second.
Still, they don't appear to be lying,\nso I'm inclined to trust them.
Bwa ha ha! How'd I know you'd say that?\nBut hey, yer the boss man, so if that's\nwhatcha wanna do, we'll do it.
It seems the rumors about you were true.\nIt was well worth seeking you out.

You are lucky to still draw breath,
considering how you threw yourself
in the middle of our brawl in an
attempt to see it ended.
That's merely the manner of person she is.\nI fear her unfailing kindness sometimes\ngets her into rash situations.
Well then. So long as you are here,\nI think we should fill you in on our\ncurrent situation as best we can.

...Well, you certainly seem to have faced
your share of hardships. Strange as it
is to say, I feel like that makes me trust
you all the more.
I understand. And if you want to return\nto your world, we'll help however we can.
It's good to meet you, Prince Alfonse.
And now, I apologize for immediately\ngetting down to business, but...
You'd like to search for Princess Veronica.
Indeed. She has lost her memory,\nand is likely rather forlorn at present.
She must have some kinda value for the\nEmpire considerin' how many men they\ngot tryin' to hunt her down.
She's gonna be safer with us.
Then let's get out there and find—
The Dyrenell Empire is attacking,\nand in vast numbers!
What?! Of all the times...\nSo much for searching for that princess.
That may not be a coincidence.\nIt's almost as if they want to stall us...
Diversion or no, we have to defend\nthe people of this town.
I also offer up my strength to your cause.
